modules.description: Provides functions for generating random bytes and seeding random number generators. Works with byte arrays and integer seeds. Used to initialize cryptographic keys and generate unique identifiers in networked applications.

Generates random byte sequences using a provided entropy source, with functions to create a buffer of a given length or fill an existing buffer. Works with the `g` type, representing a random number generator state. Used to securely populate cryptographic keys or initialize random seeds in networked applications.
